## Project Structure

```
project/
├── backend/
│   ├── app.py                   ← FastAPI server (API)
│   ├── train_traditional.py     ← Experiment 1: Logistic Regression (TF-IDF)
│   ├── train_lstm.py            ← Experiment 1: LSTM (Supervised)
│   ├── train_gru.py             ← Experiment 1: GRU (Supervised)
│   ├── train_unsupervised.py    ← Experiment 2: Autoencoder (Unsupervised)
│   ├── train_bert.py            ← Experiment 3: BERT (State-of-the-art)
│   ├── utils/
│   │   └── evaluation.py        ← Shared metrics utilities
│   ├── data/
│   │   └── dataset.csv          ← Kaggle dataset (see below)
│   ├── model/                   ← Saved models (auto-created on training)
│   └── plots/                   ← Training plots (auto-created on training)
├── frontend/
│   ├── index.html
│   └── src/
│       ├── App.jsx              ← Main React component
│       ├── App.css              ← Styles
│       ├── index.css
│       └── main.jsx
└── README.md
```

---

## Dataset

**Source:** Kaggle — AI vs Human Text Dataset  
**URL:** https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shanegerami/ai-vs-human-text

**Download instructions:**
1. Create a free Kaggle account at https://www.kaggle.com
2. Go to the dataset URL above and click **Download**
3. Extract and place `dataset.csv` inside `backend/data/`
4. Ensure the CSV has two columns: `text` (string) and `generated` (0=human, 1=AI)

---

## Dependencies

### Backend (Python 3.10+)

```bash
pip install fastapi uvicorn[standard] pandas numpy scikit-learn \
            tensorflow transformers datasets torch \
            matplotlib nltk
```

Or install from requirements:
```bash
pip install -r backend/requirements.txt
```

### Frontend (Node.js 18+)

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
```

---

## Running the Project

### Step 1 — Train the models (run each script once)

```bash
cd backend

# Experiment 1 — Supervised models
python train_traditional.py   # Logistic Regression (fast, ~1 min)
python train_lstm.py          # LSTM with 3 experiments (~10–20 min)
python train_gru.py           # GRU (~5–10 min)

# Experiment 2 — Unsupervised (Autoencoder)
python train_unsupervised.py  # (~10–20 min)

# Experiment 3 — BERT (State-of-the-art)
python train_bert.py          # (~30–60 min, GPU recommended)
```

> **Note:** Models are saved to `backend/model/`. You only need to train once.  
> Training plots are saved to `backend/plots/`.

### Step 2 — Start the backend API

```bash
cd backend
uvicorn app:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8001 --reload
```

The API will be available at: http://127.0.0.1:8001  
Interactive API docs: http://127.0.0.1:8001/docs

### Step 3 — Start the frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm run dev
```

Open your browser at: http://localhost:5173

---

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET    | `/health` | Health check |
| POST   | `/predict` | Run prediction |

### POST /predict

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "text": "Your text here...",
  "model_name": "lstm"
}
```

**`model_name` options:** `traditional`, `lstm`, `gru`, `bert`

**Response:**
```json
{
  "ai_probability": 85.3,
  "human_probability": 14.7,
  "model_used": "lstm",
  "sentences": [
    { "sentence": "First sentence.", "label": "AI", "probability": 0.9 },
    { "sentence": "Second sentence.", "label": "Human", "probability": 0.3 }
  ]
}
```

---

## GPU Acceleration (Optional)

BERT training is significantly faster on a GPU.  
If you have an NVIDIA GPU with CUDA, install:

```bash
pip install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu118
```

